.TH libidx.h 0 "June 2023" 1.0 LibIDX
.SH NAME
libidx.h \(em idx file format parsing

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libidx.h>

.SH DESCRIPTION
This library defines a series of functions for parsing the IDX file
format for stroing multidimensional arrays.
As the datatype and N-dimensionality are encoded in the file,
it is possible, with some dark magic, to define functions that work
on arrays of any dimensionality.

.SS DEFINES

.B IDX Magic Types \(em
The type of data stored in the IDX, identified by the magic number at
the start of the file
.PP
.RS
.TS
tab (@);
l lx.
IDX_MAGIC_BYTE_UNSIGNED@0x08
IDX_MAGIC_BYTE_SIGNED@0x09
IDX_MAGIC_SHORT@0x0B
IDX_MAGIC_INT@0x0C
IDX_MAGIC_FLOAT@0x0D
IDX_MAGIC_DOUBLE@0x0E
.TE
.RE

.B IDX Error Values \(em
Possible error values that may be thrown by \fIparseIDX\fR()
.PP
.RS
.TS
tab (@);
l lx.
IDX_ERROR_NO_MAGIC@1
IDX_ERROR_INCORRECT_MAGIC@2
IDX_ERROR_UNKNOWN_DATATYPE@3
IDX_ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_DIMENSIONS@4
IDX_ERROR_FILE_LENGTH_UNEXPECTED@5
IDX_ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_DATA@6
.TE
.RE

.SS STRUCTS

.B RAW_IDX \(em
Struct containing the data from an IDX file
.RS
.TP
.RI void* " data"
The data contained within the idx file.
Must be cast to the correct type before using.
.B see \fIparseIDX\fR(3)

.TP
.RI int " datasize"
The size, in bytes, of a single datapoint in the structue

.TP
.RI int " type"
The datatype of the data in the struct.
.B see \fIIDX Magic Types\fR

.TP
.RI int " dims"
The number of dimensions in the struct,
This tells you how many stars must go after the type when casting
the \fIdata\fR field

.TP
.RI int* " sizes";
An array of length \fIdims\fR containing the length of the data
structure in each dimension
.RE


.SS FUNCTIONS
.TP
int dataSize(int \fItype\fR);
.IP
RETURN
\fIsize\fR - The size in bytes

.SH APPLICATION USAGE
The IDX file format is the format used by the \fIMNIST\fR dataset.
The format stores multidimensional arrays/matrices of varying types
for usage in training and testing neural networks.

.SH FUTURE DIRECTIONS
In future this library may be expanded to contain more library
funuctions for manipulating N-dimensional arrays,
including common operations that one may one to perform on the arrays,
particularly in the dontext of training/testing neural networks.

